<br>
Nobody went to war against Hitler because he was opressing the Jews, had he not stepped out of line by attacking Poland Chamberlain's policy of appeasement and general anti-semitic feelings in Europe at the time would have allowed him to keep on rounding up homosexuals and jews and communists all he liked.<br>
<br>
Just like no one went after that Chilean guy who was doing 10x worse to his people then what Saddam was doing, because he toed the US line.  As Iraq did for many years as Saddam Hussien's secular state was being attacked by the fundamentalist shi'ite muslim government of Iran, no friend of the US at the time. Just like no one goes after the countless African despots engaging in tribal cleansing 10x worse then anything in Iraq now.<br>
<br>
This is a war of convenience.  Anyone with the sense to look at the big picture instead of engaging in comfortable tunnel vision can see it. Soothe your concience with rhetoric all you like if it helps you sleep, it's not like I can stop you.<br>
